	<http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/P78_is_identified_by> "7th /13th centuryEgyptian poet of Berber origin, he was a skilled calligrapher, a traditionist and a celebrated reciter of the Qurʾān, but his name has been immortalised by the Burda ode.  He followed the courses of the Ṣūfī Abu al-ʿAbbās Aḥmad al-Mursī (d. 686/1287) and was also involved in the first developments of the Šāḏiliyya order\n               " .
